results.name: Decimal expansion of (13-5*sqrt(5))/2.
comment: (13 - 5*sqrt(5))/2 = limit of -F(n)+(2+F(n+1))(1+F(n+2)))/(3+F(n+3)), where F = A000045 (Fibonacci numbers).
Apart from leading digits the same as A187798 and A187426. - _R. J. Mathar_, Sep 21 2013
link: Clark Kimberling, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..999
